at|^b@2|at|^^|cp|5|at|^b^*bHoward Schutzman: ^*n|
cp||at|Cohen did not touch on whether or not 1NT should still be forcing by a passed hand. I suspect that he would say it is "semi-forcing" (meaning opener can pass with 5-3-3-2 distribution and 12-14 HCP). I personally think it should still be forcing. One reason is that you need it forcing so responder can bid 1NT followed by 3 of opener's major to show a 3-card limit raise (unless you play Drury). In general, I prefer to keep things simpler by playing that bids by responder have the same meaning whether or not they are a passed hand. The only exception is that 2 over 1 bids are no longer game forcing, simply natural bids showing invitational strength.|
